  ![Four simulated iPhone screenshots showing Apple Intelligence features like the new Genmoji, smart replies, and priority notifications.](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25550596/apple_intelligence_layout.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=17.068062827225%2C0%2C65.86387434555%2C100&w=2400)
  
  ![Four simulated iPhone screenshots showing Apple Intelligence features like the new Genmoji, smart replies, and priority notifications.](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25550596/apple_intelligence_layout.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=17.068062827225%2C0%2C65.86387434555%2C100&w=2400)
  
  _Some of the Apple Intelligence features previewed during WWDC 2024._Image: Apple
  
  [![Emma Roth](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/195810/EMMA_ROTH.0.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)](https://www.theverge.com/authors/emma-roth)
  
  Emma Rothis a news writer who covers the streaming wars, consumer tech, crypto, social media, and much more. Previously, she was a writer and editor at MUO.
  
  Apple has just released the [developer betas](https://www.theverge.com/24175976/ios-18-developer-public-betas-install-how-to) for iOS 18.1, iPadOS 18.1, and macOS Sequoia 15.1, giving users access to the company’s first set of AI features.
  
  Some of the Apple Intelligence features arriving with the beta include Siri with an updated design and ability to maintain context across multiple requests, new Mail features like smart reply and email summaries, natural language search in Photos, and other tweaks, [according to _9to5Mac_](https://9to5mac.com/2024/07/29/ios-18-1-beta-1-now-available/). [_Bloomberg_ reported](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-07-07/apple-watch-series-10-ultra-3-details-bigger-screens-blood-pressure-challenge-lybjqp0q) that Apple will likely roll out some Apple Intelligence features, like Siri’s [larger AI overhaul](https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171936/apple-siri-ai-update-ios18-features-wwdc), later, running well into 2025.
  
